    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander stalks</strong> to a<strong> pestle & mortar</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and grind to a paste – this is your<strong> Thai-style paste</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, and once very hot, add the <strong>marinated</strong> <strong>tofu</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
