    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, remove the pan from the heat, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring greens </strong>and <strong>pepper strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then return the pan to the heat and cook for 4-6 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>halved</strong> <strong>sugar snaps </strong>and cook for a further 2 min or until everything is cooked with a slight bite – this is your <strong>ginger veg</strong></p>",
